---
description: UX guidance — discoverability, empty states, honest feedback
globs:
  - "gui/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Feature guidance (mandatory)

1. No first-run feature list modal. Use behavior-triggered tips (once per key in `tipsSeen`).
2. Every non-shortcut capability MUST have a second discovery path (menu, command palette, or inline hint).
3. Input placeholders MUST be copy-pasteable examples, not field name repeats.
4. Destructive actions: confirm + prefer soft-delete over hard delete.
5. Every empty state MUST include a next-step button or card.

## Visual & flow

6. One primary focus per screen (chat = message stream + composer).
7. High-frequency buttons >= 44px. No decorative widgets in send hot zone.
8. Status indicators MUST reflect real data (`#dot` ↔ daemon). No decorative green dots.
9. Modals: Esc + click overlay + explicit close — all three consistent.
10. After creating a resource (preset/template), guide user to apply it or show active state in chat.

## Command palette

11. `Ctrl+K` is the universal fallback for hidden views (presets, templates, theme, orchestrate, collab).
12. Fuzzy search by label and hint; Enter executes.
